150 grams Prawns
1 unit(s) Onion
2 unit(s) Garlic
1 unit(s) Bell Pepper
5 grams Parsley
100 grams Greek Style Cheese
2 unit(s) Ciabatta
1 sachet(s) Dried Oregano
1 pack(s) Chopped Tomato with Onion & Garlic
2 sachet(s) Dried Chilli Flakes
1 sachet(s) Vegetable Stock
½ tsp Salt
½ tsp Sugar
to taste Water
to taste Oil
to taste Pepper

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.
Halve, peel and chop the onion into small pieces.
Peel and grate the garlic (or use a garlic press)
Halve the bell pepper and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks.

In a large oven dish, mix prawns, chopped tomato, bell pepper, half the oregano, stock, chilli flakes (use less if you don't like spice), onion, garlic and 100ml water (per 2P). IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw prawns.
Season with ½ tsp salt (per 2P), ½ tsp sugar (per 2P) and pepper.
Place the whole block of Greek style cheese on top of everything.
Scatter over the remaining oregano and drizzle over a little oil.

Bake on the top shelf of the oven until bubbling and cooked through, 30-35 mins. IMPORTANT: Prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.
Meanwhile, roughly chop the parsley (stalks and all).
When everything is almost ready, halve the ciabatta lengthways then pop into the oven, cut-side up, to warm through, 2-3 mins.

Divide the baked prawns between plates.
Sprinkle over the chopped parsley.
Serve the ciabatta alongside.